      • setOntologyPrefix

        public void setOntologyPrefix(java.lang.String prefix)
        The prefix of ontology terms to be processed. Everything before the colon, e.g GO or SO or ZFA. Whilst processing, if a term is encountered without this prefix it will be discarded. See https://github.com/intermine/intermine/issues/901 for details.
        Parameters:
        prefix - prefix of the identifier for the terms of interest, eg. GO or SO or ZFA

      • configureItem

        protected void configureItem(java.lang.String termId,
                 Item item,
                 OboTerm term)
                      throws ObjectStoreException
        Set up attributes and references for the Item created from a DagTerm. Subclasses can override this method to perform extra setup, for example by casting the DagTerm to some someclass and retrieving extra attributes. Subclasses should call this inherited method first. This method will call process() for each child/component term, resulting in recursion.
        Parameters:
        termId - the term id
        item - the Item created (see termClass field for type)
        term - the source DagTerm
        Throws:
        ObjectStoreException - if an error occurs while writing to the itemWriter

      • configureSynonymItem

        protected void configureSynonymItem(OboTermSynonym syn,
                        Item item,
                        OboTerm term)
                             throws ObjectStoreException
        Set up attributes and references for the Item created from a DagTermSynonym. Subclasses can override this method to perform extra setup, for example by casting the DagTermSynonym to some someclass and retrieving extra attributes. Subclasses should call this inherited method first.
        Parameters:
        syn - the DagTermSynonym object (or a subclass of)
        item - the Item created to store the synonym
        term - the source DagTerm

        ObjectStoreException - if an error occurs while writing to the itemWriter
